{"id":"sec-week-day","html":"\n        <h1><span class=\"secnum\" id=\"sec-20.3.1.6\"><a href=\"/sec/sec-week-day.html\" title=\"link to this section\">20.3.1.6</a></span> Week\n            Day</h1>\n\n        <p class=\"normalbefore\">The weekday for a particular <a href=\"/sec/sec-time-values-and-time-range.html\">time value</a> <var>t</var>\n        is defined as</p>\n\n        <p class=\"normalBullet\">WeekDay(<i>t</i>) = (<a href=\"/sec/sec-day-number-and-time-within-day.html\">Day</a>(<i>t</i>) + 4) <a href=\"/sec/sec-algorithm-conventions.html\">modulo</a> 7</p>\n\n        <p>A weekday value of <span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">0</span> specifies Sunday; <span style=\"font-family:\n        Times New Roman\">1</span> specifies Monday; <span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">2</span> specifies Tuesday; <span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">3</span> specifies Wednesday; <span style=\"font-family: Times New\n        Roman\">4</span>&#xA0;specifies Thursday; <span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">5</span> specifies Friday; and <span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">6</span> specifies Saturday. Note that <span style=\"font-family: Times New\n        Roman\">WeekDay(0) = 4</span>, corresponding to Thursday, 01 January, 1970.</p>\n      "}